%F A335191 a(n) = Sum_{k=1..floor(b(n)/3)} Sum_{i=k..floor((b(n)-k)/2)} sign(floor((i+k)/(b(n)-i-k+1))) * chi(sqrt((b(n)/2)*(b(n)/2-i)*(b(n)/2-k)*(b(n)/2-(b(n)-i-k)))) * c(k), where chi(n) = 1 - ceiling(n) + floor(n), c is the square characteristic (A010052) and b = A335103.
%e A335191 a(1) = 1; There is one Heronian triangle with perimeter A335103(1) = 32 whose smallest side length is a square, [4,13,15].
